
Overview of noun borage

The noun borage has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. borage, tailwort, Borago officinalis -- (hairy blue-flowered European annual herb long used in herbal medicine and eaten raw as salad greens or cooked like spinach)
2. borage -- (an herb whose leaves are used to flavor sauces and punches; young leaves can be eaten in salads or cooked)
